# Patterns (.gitignore syntax) for untracked-and-gitignored files Claude Code copies
# into a new git worktree.

# Do NOT add .beads/** here. Claude Code *copies* (not symlinks) matched files into the
# worktree, so copying .beads/ would give the worktree its own forked issue database —
# writes from the worktree and from other sessions would diverge and be lost. Instead,
# leave .beads/ out: `bd` resolves the database via the shared git common dir, so a
# worktree automatically uses the main repo's single .beads/. See .claude/references/beads.md.
